race.comment: HABENARIA (8) brings decent numbers to resumption. In a top barn and was close up and Moe and Sandown Hillside, before being spelled off a plain run at Wodonga when backed off the map. Has jumped out well and will have come on. ABOVE ME (7) will be the testing material. She's been freshened off near misses at Bendigo and Echuca and has been kept up to the mark with a Mornington jumpout. HAVANA MOON (9) has an awkward gate but deserves plenty of consideration on debut. She's looked talented at the trials/jumpouts, and John Allen's booking suggests she's pleasing. HEXED (13) debuts and has won both jumpouts. JUMPIN' JEWELLETTE (10) was plain last time over 1200m, but led beaten 1.5L at Wangaratta prior. She should give a sight.
